ine beneath the red bodywork, with the Mazda emblem visible on the engine cover.\n\nThe setting returns to an urban street. The red Mazda drives forward as a pale, translucent oval or halo forms around it, visually representing its sensing or safety system. The glowing band surrounds the car’s sides and front as it moves past stone walls, sidewalks, trees, and modern buildings. From high above an intersection, the red Mazda turns through a corner while the same circular sensor rings pulse around it. A white car approaches from another street, and the overhead view makes the two vehicles’ paths clear as the red Mazda completes the turn.\n\nInside the Mazda, a young adult man with light skin, medium-length brown hair, and a slim build sits in the driver’s seat wearing a gray V-neck sweater and a seatbelt. He looks straight ahead with a concentrated expression, then glances to his left. The view changes to the driver-side mirror. In the mirror, a white car is visible behind and beside the Mazda, and small orange warning icons light up near the reflected vehicle, indicating a blind-spot alert. A sliver of the red Mazda’s body is visible along the right edge of the mirror.\n\nBack outside, the red Mazda is shown from the front with a white taxi following closely behind in the adjacent lane. The taxi sign on the roof is visible, and the red Mazda’s headlights and grille dominate the foreground while the white taxi remains behind it. The car then appears on a raised roadway or bridge with a city skyline in the background under a bright sky. The red Mazda travels smoothly along the road, separated from the city buildings by concrete barriers.\n\nThe interior returns to the same driver, now seen in profile in the front cabin. He sits upright with both hands near the steering wheel, black leather seats around him and a dashboard display screen mounted near the center. He reaches down to the center console. A close-up shows his hand using a glossy black control panel with a large round rotary knob, smaller buttons, and icons including a music note and navigation label. The dashboard screen then displays an “aha” interface with a list of options: “TechTalk,” “Facebook,” “Twitter,” “Groove Salad,” and “The Drive,” with the time “5:37” in the corner. The red selection bar highlights one of the social or audio options.\n\nThe Mazda continues on a scenic mountain road bordered by tall evergreens and rocky slopes. It drives toward the viewer along the double yellow lines, then passes close by, the red paint catching sunlight and lens-like reflections. Extreme close views blur across the front grille, headlight, and red body panels until the screen becomes mostly filled with glossy red.\n\nThe imagery then returns briefly to the earlier inspirational figures. Bruce Lee appears again in color, now wearing a bright yellow top with black trim, smiling slightly while holding one hand forward in a martial-arts gesture and the other raised behind it. Frank Lloyd Wright appears in a sepia-toned portrait, standing or leaning at a desk with an arched architectural model or structure behind him. Jackie Robinson appears in black-and-white close-up, smiling softly in his baseball cap and uniform near a dugout fence.\n\nThe final product image shows two Mazda3 cars parked on a wet scenic overlook with mountains, a river or lake, and cloudy sky in the background. A red Mazda3 sits prominently in front on the right, and a dark gray Mazda3 is behind it to the left. Large white on-screen text reads “THE ALL-NEW MAZDA3” with “STARTING AT $16,945” below, while dense fine-print legal text spans the bottom. The commercial ends with a metallic Mazda emblem glowing against a dark background, then settling above the blue word “mazda,” with the stylized word “ZOOM” appearing beneath on a diagonal white panel.",
